evaluation, Zycus stated top choice", "source": "SF Competitors__c; Next_Step__c 2026-04-20", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Lead with modular source-to-contract fit and AI-embedded value the buyer praised over Coupa.", "threat_level": "low"}, {"date": "2026-04-20", "name": "SAP Ariba", "quote": "Named in Salesforce Competitors__c; part of the 4-vendor evaluation, Zycus stated top choice", "source": "SF Competitors__c; Next_Step__c 2026-04-20", "status": "active", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Contrast Zycus's native ERP integration comfort and Teams-based Merlin intake usability against Ariba complexity.", "threat_level": "low"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09; Next_Step__c 2026-06-18", "at_risk": true, "summary": "Sam Langsjo is an enthusiastic advocate who rates Zycus highest but lacks authority and access to the budget owner, and engagement has cooled since 2026-04-09 with no reply to the 2026-06-18 check-in. The prior champion Benjamin Rainsford departed the company around Nov 2025.", "champion": "Sam Langsjo", "strength": "weak"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Benjamin Rainsford", "risk": "Departed the company around Nov 2025; no longer involved.", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "brainsford@jw.org", "title": "Procurement Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Positive; original champion who organized the demo and drove Jul-Oct 2025 engagement.", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-11-21"}, {"name": "Jacob Blane", "risk": "Not engaged since the 2025-09-26 budget call; unclear current involvement.", "role": "Decision Maker", "title": "Strategic Account Director", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Positive on commercials; noted 'price on par with expectations' but costs 'harder to justify' with volunteer personnel.", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-09-26"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma discovery 2025-07-01", "Avoma demo 2025-08-04", "Avoma budget call 2025-09-26", "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09"], "narrative": "The buyer articulated clear qualitative pain, roughly 10,000 contracts globally managed across hundreds of entities, an ERP contract 'black hole', and manual decentralized processes (Sam and Ben, Avoma discovery 2025-07-01 and demo 2025-08-04), plus a centralization program spanning 84 branches in 84 countries. But no savings, cycle-time, or ROI number was ever quantified. Jacob Blane flagged budget sensitivity on 2025-09-26: costs are 'harder to justify because personnel are volunteers.' Zycus offered a full ROI business case but never closed the loop with Watchtower's spend data, so the value stayed qualitative and lost to status-quo inertia; quantifying it is the top move."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF OpportunityContactRole (Benjamin Rainsford, Decision Maker)", "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09", "Next_Step__c 2026-06-18"], "narrative": "Benjamin Rainsford (Procurement Manager, Decision Maker per Contact Role) was the original champion who organized the demo and drove engagement Jul-Oct 2025, but he departed the company around Nov 2025. Sam Langsjo took over as the active advocate: he praised Zycus as 'by far the best' vendor, escalated the pilot internally, and pushed buy-in Feb-Apr 2026. What developed is genuine preference for Zycus; what is missing is authority and access to the budget owner. Sam admitted on 2026-04-09 that 'the hardest time with the business is it's not the business, it's just the internal stakeholders. A lot of good ideas get stopped because of that.' He is a coach without power, and engagement has cooled since 2026-04-09 with no reply to the 2026-06-18 check-in."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["SF Competitors__c", "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09", "Next_Step__c 2026-04-20", "Avoma connect 2026-01-07"], "narrative": "The decisive competitor is the status quo, the existing ERP-based contract management the Ramapo contract stakeholders are 'happy with' without Zycus's added features (Sam, 2026-04-09), reinforced by an internal build option (five AI use cases being developed in-house, 2026-01-07). Among named external vendors (Coupa, GEP Worldwide, SAP Ariba), Zycus is the buyer-stated front-runner: Sam said on 2026-04-20 that of four vendors 'we are top choice given demo quality and CLM tools,' so the external field is a low current threat. We win only by defeating do-nothing, reframing value as the cost of manual contract management and tail-spend leakage against the pushed close date, delivered to the budget owner."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma demo 2025-08-04", "Avoma budget call 2025-09-26", "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09"], "narrative": "The confirmed pain is decentralized, manual contract and procurement management across 84 branches with no standardized supplier risk system and legal-heavy manual contracting (Grace and Ben framed this on 2025-08-04). Sam confirmed the CLM and tail-spend opportunity, and Jacob on 2025-09-26 noted a large upcoming construction project that will nearly double US spend, exposing tail-spend that autonomous negotiation could address. The inferred but unowned tension is that the Ramapo contract team is satisfied with the current ERP workflow, so the pain is real at the transformation level but not felt as urgent by the stakeholders who must approve."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma budget call 2025-09-26", "Avoma connect 2026-01-07"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics were never reached. An NDA is in place (Mike referenced 'we are under NDA' on 2025-09-26), and Zycus proposed a fixed-fee implementation with a scoping session, but no MSA/SOW, legal, procurement, or InfoSec track ever opened because the deal never cleared internal justification. A homegrown-ERP integration deep-dive was floated as a separate 'prove the how' session (Mike, 2026-01-07) but not scheduled. Visibility would come only after the buyer commits to a pilot; there is no contract-expiration forcing function on record."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma budget call 2025-09-26", "Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09", "SF OpportunityContactRole (Jacob Blane, Decision Maker)"], "narrative": "The economic buyer was never identified or engaged in twelve months. Sam Langsjo and Nico are mid-level procurement contacts without budget authority; on 2026-04-09 Sam said 'we'll talk to our boss later today or later this week' about whether to readdress the pilot, but that senior leader was never named to Zycus and never joined a call. Jacob Blane (Strategic Account Director, Decision Maker per Contact Role) engaged on commercials on 2025-09-26 ('price on par with expectations') but did not present as the final budget owner. The evidence shows budget authority sits above Sam with an unnamed senior leader; reaching that person is the single highest-leverage gap to close."}, "decision_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma pilot connect 2026-04-09", "Next_Step__c 2026-04-20"], "narrative": "The process the buyer is actually running is an internal build-versus-buy deliberation gated by stakeholder buy-in, not a formal vendor bake-off. Reading the call sequence, Zycus ran discovery (2025-07-01), a broad demo with the CD/IT team (2025-08-04), a budget/pricing session (2025-09-26), a relaunch with new leads Sam and Nico (2026-01-07), and a pilot-scoping call (2026-04-09) where the buyer reported the internal stakeholders would not approve the move. Sam owns internal advocacy but must clear his boss and the Ramapo contract stakeholders. The approval chain runs Sam/Nico -> their manager (budget owner) -> contract stakeholders, and it stalled at that manager gate."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma demo 2025-08-04", "Avoma connect 2026-01-07", "AIS_Why__c"], "narrative": "Criteria are well un